# UDS Figma Component Card

Specification for the canvas layout used on every component page in the UDS Components Figma file (and its testbed). One frame per component, named `udc-<id>-page`, holding seven cards in a fixed order. The component sets, sub-components, and instance previews live INSIDE these cards ŌĆö they are never loose top-level nodes.

## Why this rule exists

Component pages used to be a pile of unlabeled component sets sprawled at random positions. This rule defines the canonical "card" treatment so:
- Every page reads the same way (same card order, same eyebrows, same status colors)
- Future agents and skills produce identical output without re-deciding layout questions
- A designer can edit the visual template once and every agent run picks it up
- Token bindings are forced ŌĆö no raw hex anywhere

## Direction of data flow (CRITICAL)

This rule covers **code ŌåÆ Figma** writes, opposite of most UDS sync work. The card builder READS from `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/spec.json` and WRITES card structure into the UDS Components Figma file. It must follow:

- [`uds-figma-write-safety.mdc`](./uds-figma-write-safety.mdc) ŌĆö Figma writes are denied by default; this skill writes only when the user explicitly invokes it. Every write must produce the standard "Figma write summary" report.
- [`uds-source-of-truth.mdc`](./uds-source-of-truth.mdc) ŌĆö `uds-docs/uds/` is read-only for this skill. Never modifies spec/status/changelog/impl/css under that path. Reads only.
- [`uds-figma-preflight.mdc`](./uds-figma-preflight.mdc) ŌĆö discovery and read-only inspection always come before any write.

If an audit finding suggests the spec or component CSS should change, surface it as a recommendation; do not edit `uds-docs/uds/`. The authorized write paths into `uds-docs/uds/` are the named Figma-sync skills (`import-figma-tokens`, `sync-figma-component-spec`, `sync-figma-component-status`, `link-figma-nodes`, `new-component`) ŌĆö not this one.

