## Status ŌåÆ token map

Status comes from `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/status.json` (`current` field) as the primary source. The page-name stoplight prefix in the Figma file is a secondary signal ŌĆö they should agree, but if they disagree, use the JSON status and surface the mismatch to the user (do not auto-correct the Figma page name; that's [`sync-figma-component-status`](../skills/sync-figma-component-status/SKILL.md)'s job).

The Figma prefix ŌåÆ `status.json.current` mapping is canonical in
[`uds-figma-preflight.mdc`](./uds-figma-preflight.mdc) ┬¦"Stoplight status
mapping". For the component-card pill, the additional mapping
(status ŌåÆ pill label + color tokens) is:

| Status (in `status.json` `current` field) | Pill label | Color tokens |
|---|---|---|
| `in-progress` | `IN PROGRESS` | text/border/icon/surface `-warning` |
| `blocked` | `BLOCKED` | `-error` |
| `review` | `IN REVIEW` | `-warning` (yellow tone via mode) |
| `production` | `PRODUCTION READY` | `-success` |
| `placeholder` | `NOT STARTED` | `-tertiary` (no specific status color, all neutral) |

For placeholder pages: HEADER stays dark, but the eyebrow number, top accent strip, kicker, and pill use neutral tokens (`border-tertiary`, `text-secondary`) instead of a status color. Don't fake an orange/green for placeholder.

